Which fat soluble vitamin supplements reduce cardiovascular disease? There is evidence that vitamin E and vitamin C supplements may reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease.
Do Vitamin D supplements reduce cardiovascular risk? There is currently no good evidence that vitamin D supplements reduce cardiovascular risk.

The supplementation of diet with which fat soluble vitamins has been shown to reduce cardiovascular disease? The supplementation of diet with vitamin E has been shown to reduce cardiovascular disease.

Do Vitamin E supplements reduce cardiovascular risk? There is inconclusive evidence on whether vitamin E supplements reduce cardiovascular risk. Some studies suggest that vitamin E supplements may modestly reduce the risk of heart disease, while other studies find no benefit. More research is needed to determine whether vitamin E supplements are effective in reducing cardiovascular risk.
Do Vitamin A supplements reduce cardiovascular risk? There is no evidence that vitamin A supplements reduce cardiovascular risk.
